B.Qo=new A.az(B.K,["intro-1","Introduction","About Cadet Biathlon","General","Biathlon is one of the most popular aspects of tri-service cadet training. It is a sport combining cross-country skiing (or running) with precision air rifle shooting. The Championship Series operates in four stages:\n\n\u2022 Stage 1 \u2013 Corps/Squadron Championship & Zone Selection\n\u2022 Stage 2 \u2013 Zone Championship & Provincial/Territorial Selection\n\u2022 Stage 3 \u2013 Provincial/Territorial Championship & National Selection\n\u2022 Stage 4 \u2013 National Championship\n\nRace fees are not charged to Corps/Squadrons at any stage."],t.R)
B.QE=new A.az(B.K,["cat-1","Competitor Categories","Junior Boys & Girls","Eligibility","A Junior is a cadet who will NOT reach their 15th birthday two days after the final day of the National Cadet Biathlon Championship."],t.R)
B.Qp=new A.az(B.K,["cat-2","Competitor Categories","Senior Boys & Girls","Eligibility","A Senior is a cadet older than a Junior who will NOT reach their 17th birthday two days after the final day of the National Cadet Biathlon Championship."],t.R)
B.Ql=new A.az(B.K,["cat-3","Competitor Categories","Youth Men & Women","Eligibility","A Youth is a cadet who is not a Junior or Senior and will NOT reach their 19th birthday two days after the final day of the National Cadet Biathlon Championship."],t.R)
B.Qc=new A.az(B.K,["cat-4","Competitor Categories","General Eligibility","Eligibility","To be eligible, a cadet must have joined the CCO no later than 31 December of the training year and must not have reached their 19th birthday two days after the final day of the National Biathlon Championship. The cadet must be considered an active member of their unit \u2014 the CO is the authority to confirm this."],t.R)
B.Qx=new A.az(B.K,["team-1","Team Composition","Unit Team Types","Teams","The following team types are recognized:\n\n\u2022 Open Male Team \u2013 Two male cadets in any category\n\u2022 Open Female Team \u2013 Two female cadets in any category\n\u2022 Junior Male Team \u2013 Two male cadets both in the Junior category\n\u2022 Junior Female Team \u2013 Two female cadets both in the Junior category\n\u2022 Open Mixed Team \u2013 One cadet of each gender in any category\n\u2022 Junior Mixed Team \u2013 One cadet of each gender both in Junior category\n\nNote: Open/Junior Mixed Teams compete as Male teams in team races."],t.R)
B.Qe=new A.az(B.K,["team-2","Team Composition","Stage 4 Provincial Relay & Patrol Teams","Teams","\u2022 Provincial Male Team \u2013 One Open Male + one Junior Male (4 members)\n\u2022 Provincial Female Team \u2013 One Open Female + one Junior Female (4 members)\n\u2022 Provincial Composite Team \u2013 Individuals not on a complete team (2 members)"],t.R)
B.QS=new A.az(B.K,["team-3","Team Composition","Substitutions","Teams","At Stages 3 & 4, a cadet may only be replaced by an eligible cadet from the same corps/squadron for the following reasons:\n\n\u2022 Parental request\n\u2022 Withdrawal from the CCO\n\u2022 Medical problem\n\u2022 Discipline problem\n\nA notice of intent must be forwarded to the OPI no less than 24 hours prior to the start of competition."],t.R)
B.Qf=new A.az(B.K,["race-1","Race Specifications","Run & Shoot Specifications (Stages 1 & 2)","Race Rules","\u2022 Firing Distance: 10 metres (Air Rifle)\n\u2022 Positions: Prone or Prone and Standing (unsupported)\n\u2022 Rifle: .177 cal Air Rifle\n\u2022 Loading: Single round (5-round clips PROHIBITED \u2013 10 min penalty)\n\u2022 Time Limit: No time limit\n\u2022 Target: Biathlon Air Rifle Target (BT100) at 10 m; centre 18\u201320 cm above shooting ramp\n\u2022 Ammunition: DND issued only\n\u2022 Safety glasses/shatterproof eyeglasses recommended"],t.R)
B.Qq=new A.az(B.K,["race-2","Race Specifications","Competition Distances by Category","Race Rules","Individual races (all categories): Run \u2013 3 km | Ski \u2013 5 km\n\nYOUTH MEN/WOMEN (Stages 3 & 4):\n\u2022 Short Sprint: 1.5 or 2.25 km\n\u2022 Sprint: 7.5 km (Men) / 6 km (Women)\n\u2022 Individual: 12.5 km (Men) / 10 km (Women)\n\u2022 Mass Start: 10 km (Men) / 7.5 km (Women)\n\nSENIOR BOYS/GIRLS:\n\u2022 Sprint: 6 km | Individual: 7.5 km | Mass Start: 7.5 km\n\nJUNIOR BOYS/GIRLS:\n\u2022 Sprint: 4.5 km | Individual: 6 km | Mass Start: 6 km\n\u2022 Team Relay: 2\xd74.5 km or 4\xd74.5 km"],t.R)
B.QD=new A.az(B.K,["race-3","Race Specifications","Shot Penalties","Race Rules","For every target left standing after all rounds are fired:\n\n\u2022 Juniors: 40-second time penalty OR 150 m penalty loop\n\u2022 Seniors & Youth: 60-second time penalty OR 150 m penalty loop\n\nIn Relay competitions: First 5 rounds fired; if targets remain, up to 3 spare rounds may be used (hand-loaded one by one \u2014 not from a magazine)."],t.R)
B.Qs=new A.az(B.K,["shoot-1","Shooting Regulations","Prone Position Rules","Shooting","In the prone position:\n\n\u2022 The rifle may only be in contact with hands, shoulder, and cheek\n\u2022 The lower side of the wrist of the supporting arm MUST be distinctly raised from the ground\n\u2022 No part of body, clothing, or equipment may protrude over the lane boundary lines while shooting\n\u2022 The rifle muzzle must extend over the firing line"],t.R)
B.Qa=new A.az(B.K,["shoot-2","Shooting Regulations","Standing Position Rules","Shooting","In the standing position:\n\n\u2022 Competitors must stand WITHOUT any support\n\u2022 Only hands, shoulder, cheek, and chest area next to shoulder may contact the rifle\n\u2022 The supporting arm may be held against chest or propped against hip\n\u2022 Removing skis while shooting is PROHIBITED\n\u2022 Placing any object under the skis is PROHIBITED"],t.R)
B.QA=new A.az(B.K,["shoot-3","Shooting Regulations","Shooting Safety Rules","Shooting","\u2022 Shooting permitted ONLY on the range during authorized times\n\u2022 The rifle muzzle must be over the firing line from start to end of each bout\n\u2022 No one is permitted forward of the firing line when range is open\n\u2022 Rifles loaded/unloaded ONLY with barrel pointing at targets OR pointing up\n\u2022 When moving between lanes: unload rifle and place on back first\n\u2022 All shots must be aimed and fired ONLY at the competitor's own targets"],t.R)
B.Qu=new A.az(B.K,["shoot-4","Shooting Regulations","Safety Check After Each Bout (Air Rifle)","Shooting","After each shooting bout:\n\n\u2022 Open the bolt \u2014 no round may be left in the chamber\n\u2022 The pump lever does NOT need to be opened after each bout\n\nAt the END of training:\n\u2022 Perform a dryfire, then open the bolt and pump lever with barrel toward targets or up\n\u2022 Remove ALL ammunition from stock before leaving the range\n\nCOACH responsibility: Confirm pump lever is open, bolt is open, and no round in chamber before moving rifle."],t.R)
B.Qj=new A.az(B.K,["shoot-5","Shooting Regulations","Misfires & Equipment Issues","Shooting","MISFIRES / LOST ROUNDS:\n\u2022 Replace from spare rounds if carried\n\u2022 If no spares available: raise hand and loudly say \"Ammunition\"\n\u2022 A range official will bring rounds from the team's reserve\n\nDAMAGED RIFLE:\n\u2022 Repairs may be done by the competitor, competition armourer, or a range official only\n\u2022 If unfixable, exchange for the team's pre-inspected reserve rifle from the rifle rack\n\u2022 No time adjustment is given for repairs or exchanges"],t.R)
B.Qm=new A.az(B.K,["shoot-6","Shooting Regulations","Air Rifle Loading Procedure","Shooting","\u26a0\ufe0f AMENDED RULE (Air Rifle / Run & Shoot):\n\n\u2022 Pumping the rifle IS part of the loading procedure\n\u2022 Rifles must be unloaded DURING pumping \u2014 bolt must be fully to the rear\n\u2022 Pellets may only be inserted and bolt closed AFTER pumping\n\u2022 Loading out of correct sequence = 2-minute penalty per occurrence\n\n5-round clips (magazines) are PROHIBITED.\nUse of a 5-round clip = 10-minute penalty (Rule 5.11.c)"],t.R)
B.Q8=new A.az(B.K,["shoot-7","Shooting Regulations","Lane Width (Air Rifle \u2013 Amended)","Shooting","Standard smallbore lane width: 2.75 m \u2013 3.0 m\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f AIR RIFLE AMENDMENT:\nLane width for air rifle/run & shoot events: 1.25 m \u2013 1.5 m\nLane markings may use any appropriate means (flagging tape, paint, etc.)\nT-Posts are recommended but not required."],t.R)
B.QQ=new A.az(B.K,["coach-1","Coaching","Adult Coach Requirements","Coaching","\u2022 An adult coach must be a CAF member or Civilian Instructor (CI)\n\u2022 Civilian volunteers CANNOT be the adult coach\n\u2022 Up to 6 competitors \u2192 1 adult coach required\n\u2022 7\u201312 competitors \u2192 2 adult coaches required\n\nDuring competition, the adult coach is responsible for:\n\u2022 Care and custody of all rifles and equipment\n\u2022 Providing rifle/ammunition at the lane or rack before competitor arrives\n\u2022 After competitor leaves: retrieve rifle, ensure bolt is to the rear, pump lever open, magazine removed, muzzle pointing up\n\u2022 Resetting the target\n\u2022 Coaches may zero rifles and adjust sights between bouts (except in Patrol Race)\n\u2022 Coaches may coach skiing during all races except Patrol\n\u2022 Coaches may use radios unless OC directs otherwise"],t.R)
B.Qd=new A.az(B.K,["coach-2","Coaching","Cadet Coach Requirements","Coaching","\u2022 A cadet coach must be 16\u201318 years of age at the time of the National Championship\n\u2022 Up to 6 competitors \u2192 1 cadet coach may assist\n\u2022 7\u201312 competitors \u2192 2 cadet coaches may assist\n\nCadet coaches CANNOT sign for rifles and equipment.\nThey assist the adult coach with duties before, during, and after competition."],t.R)
B.Qv=new A.az(B.K,["coach-3","Coaching","Coaching Prohibitions on Range","Coaching","\u26d4 PROHIBITED ON THE RANGE (10 m zone of silence on each side):\n\n\u2022 Giving competitors any acoustic or visual information\n\u2022 Using radio or any communication method to pass information\n\u2022 Passing information from the shooting butts to coaches or competitors during zeroing or competition\n\nGeneral expressions of applause or disappointment by spectators are allowed."],t.R)
B.QK=new A.az(B.K,["pen-1","Penalties","Reprimands","Penalties","A reprimand is issued for:\n\n\u2022 Jeopardizing the honour or reputation of the CCO\n\u2022 Insulting CCO members or guests\n\u2022 Removing a rifle from the firing line with bolt closed \u2014 1st infraction (reprimand to coach)\n\u2022 Bolt closed while rifle is on the rack \u2014 1st infraction (reprimand to coach)"],t.R)
B.Qz=new A.az(B.K,["pen-2","Penalties","30-Second Penalty","Penalties","Applied when:\n\n\u2022 A competitor starts a Pursuit race up to 3 seconds BEFORE their assigned start time."],t.R)
B.QH=new A.az(B.K,["pen-3","Penalties","1-Minute Penalty","Penalties","Applied for:\n\n\u2022 Not giving way at the first request by an overtaking competitor\n\u2022 Very minor violation of fair play or sportsmanship requirements"],t.R)
B.Qw=new A.az(B.K,["pen-4","Penalties","2-Minute Penalty","Penalties","Applied for:\n\n\u2022 Every penalty loop (from shot-penalties) NOT done immediately after the shooting bout\n\u2022 Every round NOT fired if an athlete leaves the range before firing all required rounds (having not hit all targets)\n\u2022 Minor violation of fair play or sportsmanship\n\u2022 During Patrol: skiing with >30 m between first and last members when entering/exiting range\n\u2022 During Patrol: cross-firing before hitting all 5 targets or before teammate opens bolt\n\u2022 Bolt left closed on exit rack\n\u2022 Shooting more than 5 rounds per bout (Individual/Sprint/Pursuit/Mass Start) \u2014 per extra round\n\u2022 Remaining in incorrect shooting position after being warned\n\u2022 Leaving a live round in rifle at conclusion of a bout \u2014 1st infraction\n\u2022 Starting >3 seconds early in a pursuit\n\u2022 \u26a0\ufe0f Improper air rifle loading (pumping with bolt closed) \u2014 per occurrence"],t.R)
B.Qi=new A.az(B.K,["pen-5","Penalties","5-Minute Penalty","Penalties","Applied for:\n\n\u2022 Receiving prohibited assistance from team staff or non-competing team athletes\n\u2022 During Patrol: two competitors firing on the same set of targets simultaneously"],t.R)
B.QO=new A.az(B.K,["pen-6","Penalties","10-Minute Penalty","Penalties","Applied for:\n\n\u2022 Avoiding start or finish controls\n\u2022 Competing with skis or rifle not properly marked\n\u2022 Modifying inspected/marked equipment in a prohibited way\n\u2022 Using wrong start number deliberately or in error\n\u2022 Exchanging BOTH skis during competition\n\u2022 Skiing the course in improper sequence\n\u2022 During Patrol: failing to fire a shooting bout (per member)\n\u2022 During Patrol: each ski loop not completed by the team\n\u2022 \u26a0\ufe0f Use of a 5-round clip (magazine) with air rifle"],t.R)
B.Qh=new A.az(B.K,["pen-7","Penalties","Disqualification","Penalties","An athlete is disqualified for:\n\n\u2022 Competing while ineligible\n\u2022 Receiving prohibited assistance from team staff\n\u2022 Deviating from the marked trail and gaining time\n\u2022 Using propulsion other than skis, poles, and own muscular force\n\u2022 Not carrying rifle with barrel pointing up while skiing on range\n\u2022 Seriously obstructing another athlete\n\u2022 Accepting unauthorized equipment repair assistance\n\u2022 Applying substances to change ski glide during competition\n\u2022 Failing to shoot in the correct sequence of positions\n\u2022 Using a second magazine instead of hand-loading spare rounds\n\u2022 Violating any shooting safety regulation (Rule 8.5)\n\u2022 Committing a serious fair play violation\n\u2022 Leaving a live round in rifle at conclusion of a bout \u2014 2nd infraction"],t.R)
B.QC=new A.az(B.K,["pen-8","Penalties","Coach Ban","Penalties","A coach is banned from coaching for the remainder of a competition for:\n\n\u2022 Violating any shooting safety regulations (Rule 8.5)\n\u2022 Removing a rifle from the firing line with bolt closed \u2014 2nd infraction\n\u2022 Bolt closed while rifle is on rack \u2014 2nd infraction\n\nThe ban stays in effect until Final Competition results are issued."],t.R)
B.QJ=new A.az(B.K,["ski-1","Course & Skiing","General Skiing Rules","Course",'\u2022 Competitors must ski the entire course in the correct sequence and direction\n\u2022 Only skis, poles, and own muscular force permitted for propulsion\n\u2022 All skiing techniques are permitted\n\nPASSING: Yell "Track" to pass. Competitor being passed MUST yield immediately.\nException: No obligation to yield in the last 50 m before the finish or hand-over zone.\n\nWRONG COURSE: Return to the point of error (no penalty unless other competitors are obstructed).'],t.R)
B.QP=new A.az(B.K,["ski-2","Course & Skiing","Penalty Loop","Course","\u2022 Length: 150 m (\xb15 m), measured along the inside perimeter\n\u2022 Width: 6 m, oval shape\n\u2022 Located immediately after the shooting range (no more than 60 m from the right edge)\n\u2022 Competitors must ski the loop ONCE for every missed target IMMEDIATELY after the bout\n\u2022 Penalty loops CANNOT be completed at a later time\n\u2022 The competitor exiting the penalty loop has right of way over a competitor entering"],t.R)
B.Qr=new A.az(B.K,["ski-3","Course & Skiing","Equipment Exchange Rules","Course","\u2022 One broken ski may be exchanged (or both if both are provably broken by accident)\n\u2022 Poles and straps may be exchanged repeatedly\n\u2022 On the range, equipment may only be passed by competition officials\n\u2022 Competitors CANNOT change ski glide performance during competition\n\u2022 Rifle repairs on range: permitted by competition armourer or range official only\n\u2022 Rifle exchange: on the range only, for the team's pre-marked reserve rifle"],t.R)
B.QB=new A.az(B.K,["weather-1","Weather","Temperature & Wind Chill Rules","Safety","\u26a0\ufe0f Competitions must NOT start if air temperature is colder than \u201320\xb0C (measured at coldest part of site, 1.5 m above ground).\n\nIf colder than \u201315\xb0C, wind-chill and humidity must be considered. The Competition Jury will decide whether to start, modify, or stop the competition.\n\nTemperature is measured at 1.5 m at the coldest competition area.\nWind speed is measured at 1.5 m on the range."],t.R)
B.QI=new A.az(B.K,["protest-1","Protests","How to Submit a Protest","Administration","\u2022 Protests must be submitted in writing to the competition secretary or TD using the official Protest Form\n\u2022 Protest fee: as determined by OPI at Stages 1\u20133 | $20.00 at Stage 4\n\u2022 Fee is refunded if the protest is upheld\n\nTIMING:\n\u2022 Eligibility protests: any time up to end of protest period for that competition\n\u2022 Rule/official/result protests: from start of zeroing until 15 minutes after Provisional Results are posted\n\nAPPEAL: If Competition Jury does not uphold the protest, a written appeal may be lodged within 30 min (Stages 3 & 4) or within 24 hours (other stages) to the applicable RCSU OPI."],t.R)
B.Qt=new A.az(B.K,["range-1","Range Procedures (Annex C)","Junior Boys/Girls \u2013 Range Procedure","Range","After firing the last shot of each bout:\n\n1. Open the bolt\n2. Place the rifle on the firing point mat\n3. Notify coach (pump lever opening NOT required between bouts)\n\nPENALTY: If the rifle is left with the bolt NOT opened = 2-minute penalty per violation\n\nCOACH SAFETY CHECK before moving the rifle:\n\u2022 Pump lever is open\n\u2022 Bolt has been opened\n\u2022 No round in the chamber"],t.R)
B.Qy=new A.az(B.K,["range-2","Range Procedures (Annex C)","Senior/Youth \u2013 Rack to Rack Carry","Range","The Rack to Rack Carry applies to Senior and Youth categories at Stage 4 (and optionally at Stages 2 & 3 where capable).\n\nFor each bout, the coach will provide the competitor:\n\u2022 A bowl containing the required number of pellets\n\u2022 Magazines may be provided on the rifle's magazine rail (if equipped),\n  placed on the mat for prone, or handed to the athlete for standing\n\nAfter last shot of each bout:\n1. Open the bolt\n2. Place rifle on the mat with barrel pointing toward targets\n3. Exit the firing point and range in the normal manner\n\nStanding bout: After last shot, perform a safety check, leave the bolt open, and wait for coach."],t.R)
B.N2=s([B.Qo,B.QE,B.Qp,B.Ql,B.Qc,B.Qx,B.Qe,B.QS,B.Qf,B.Qq,B.QD,B.Qs,B.Qa,B.QA,B.Qu,B.Qj,B.Qm,B.Q8,B.QQ,B.Qd,B.Qv,B.QK,B.Qz,B.QH,B.Qw,B.Qi,B.QO,B.Qh,B.QC,B.QJ,B.QP,B.Qr,B.QB,B.QI,B.Qt,B.Qy],t.H7)
B.U4=new A.oO("Biathlon Rules",B.N2,null)
B.QM=new A.az(B.K,["m-safety-1","Safety Regulations","The Four Core Safety Rules","Safety","1. TREAT EVERY RIFLE AS IF IT IS LOADED.\n2. ALWAYS POINT THE MUZZLE IN A SAFE DIRECTION.\n3. DO NOT PUT YOUR FINGER ON THE TRIGGER UNTIL READY TO SHOOT.\n4. BE SURE OF YOUR TARGET AND WHAT IS BEYOND IT."],t.R)
B.Q9=new A.az(B.K,["m-safety-2","Safety Regulations","General Safety Rules","Safety","\u2022 Safety glasses or shatterproof eyeglasses MUST be worn at all times on the range.\n\u2022 Hearing protection is recommended.\n\u2022 Rifles must have a safety rod/string in place when entering or leaving the range.\n\u2022 When not in use, rifles must have the pump handle open, bolt to the rear, and safety on.\n\u2022 Muzzles must always be pointed downrange or up."],t.R)
B.Qg=new A.az(B.K,["m-range-1","Range Commands","The Loading & Firing Sequence","Range",'\u2022 "RANGE ALERT" - Stop all activity, rifles on the mat, muzzles downrange.\n\u2022 "RELAY #, ON TO YOUR FIRING POINTS" - Competitors move to assigned lanes.\n\u2022 "PREPARATION PERIOD START" - Competitors may handle rifles, adjust equipment, but NOT load.\n\u2022 "LOAD" - Place a pellet in the chamber, but do NOT close the bolt.\n\u2022 "FIRE" - Close the bolt and commence firing.\n\u2022 "CEASE FIRE" - Stop firing immediately. Open the bolt, leave the rifle on the mat.\n\u2022 "UNLOAD / ACTION CLEAR" - Perform safety check, insert safety rod, wait for inspection.'],t.R)
B.QF=new A.az(B.K,["m-stage-1","Competition Stages","Stage 1 \u2013 Corps/Squadron","General","Objective: Select a team for Stage 2.\n\u2022 Competitors: Any active cadet with valid medical.\n\u2022 Course of Fire: OPI's discretion.\n\u2022 Position: Prone (Standing optional).\n\u2022 Funding: Provided by the local unit."],t.R)
B.QT=new A.az(B.K,["m-stage-2","Competition Stages","Stage 2 \u2013 Zone Championship","General","Objective: Select Unit Teams and Individuals for Provincial Championship.\n\u2022 Team Strength: 5 competitors (minimum 2 Juniors).\n\u2022 Scoring: Top 4 scores count towards the team total.\n\u2022 HPS: 400 per competitor (1600 per team).\n\u2022 Time Limit: 30 min (20-shot relay) / 15 min (10-shot relay).\n\u2022 Awards: Zone Marksmanship Championship pin."],t.R)
B.QR=new A.az(B.K,["m-stage-3","Competition Stages","Stage 3 \u2013 Provincial Championship","General","Objective: Select top team and individuals for Nationals.\n\u2022 Course of Fire: 90 pellets total (60 prone, 30 standing).\n\u2022 Targets: Electronic targets (SIUS) are standard.\n\u2022 HPS: 981 per competitor.\n\u2022 Awards: Provincial Marksmanship Championship pin."],t.R)
B.QL=new A.az(B.K,["m-equip-1","Equipment","Approved Rifles","Equipment","\u2022 Daisy 853C / Avanti 853C are the only approved rifles.\n\u2022 Modifications: Adjustable butt plates are permitted (amended 2018).\n\u2022 Single pellet loading only. Use of 5-pellet clips is PROHIBITED at all stages."],t.R)
B.Qk=new A.az(B.K,["m-equip-2","Equipment","Authorized Gear","Equipment","\u2022 Shooting Jackets: May be worn (must be flexible/pliable).\n\u2022 Gloves: May be worn on the supporting hand.\n\u2022 Slings: Permitted for prone shooting.\n\u2022 Measuring Tape: Permitted for determining foot placement in standing position (cannot be under the foot while firing)."],t.R)
B.Qn=new A.az(B.K,["m-pen-1","Warnings & Penalties","Warnings","Penalties","A warning will be issued for:\n\u2022 Firing position or lane violations.\n\u2022 Minor safety violations (improper loading, leaving line without safety rod).\n\u2022 Not opening the bolt when not handling rifle in standing position (2019 Amendment).\n\u2022 Improper sports etiquette."],t.R)
B.QN=new A.az(B.K,["m-pen-2","Warnings & Penalties","Points Penalties","Penalties",'\u2022 Subsequent Minor Safety Violation: 5-point penalty.\n\u2022 Major Safety Violation: 10-point penalty (no warning).\n\u2022 Cross-fire: Loss of max value (10 pts) + 2-point penalty per shot.\n\u2022 Shot after "Cease Fire": Highest value shot discarded + 10-point penalty.\n\u2022 Extra shot fired: Highest value discarded + 2-point penalty per extra shot.'],t.R)
B.QG=new A.az(B.K,["m-pen-3","Warnings & Penalties","Disqualifications","Penalties","Immediate DQ for:\n\u2022 Safety violation causing imminent danger to self or others.\n\u2022 Taking part while ineligible.\n\u2022 Concealing a known violation.\n\u2022 Using prohibited assistance or non-conforming equipment/pellets."],t.R)
B.Qb=new A.az(B.K,["m-score-1","Scoring","Tie-Breaking Rules","Administration",'Ties are broken in this order:\n1. Highest score of the last 10-shot series (working backwards).\n2. Highest number of 10s, 9s, 8s, etc.\n3. Highest number of "Inner 10s" (tens not touching the 9 ring).\n4. If decimal scoring used: highest decimal score of last 10-shot series.'],t.R)
B.Lm=s([B.QM,B.Q9,B.Qg,B.QF,B.QT,B.QR,B.QL,B.Qk,B.Qn,B.QN,B.QG,B.Qb],t.H7)
